article.headline: Florida Atlantic 73, Louisiana-Monroe 62
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Carlos Monroe had a game-high 19 points to help Florida Atlantic beat Louisiana-Monroe 73-62 on Saturday. Jeff Parmer added 18 for Florida Atlantic (8-9, 4-3 Sun Belt Conference) and Paul Graham and DeAndre Rice finished with 14 and 12 points, respectively. Jonas Brown led Louisiana-Monroe (11-8, 5-2) with 17 points. Two other Warhawks were also in double digits, Lance Brasher with 14 and Brandon Roberts with 11. The Warhawks shot 40.4 percent from the floor while the Owls shot 58 percent.
